tafsir[12]{c,v,t}:
  70,12,"And his spouse and his brother) his full brother"
  70,13,"(And his kin) and his clan and relatives (that harboured him) to whom he belongs"
  70,15,"(But nay!) truly this will not deliver him from the punishment-this is an answer to him-(for lo! it is the fire of hell"
  70,16,"Eager to roast) the entire body; it is also said that this means: it will pluck out the hands and feet as well as all the other members of the body;"
  70,18,"(And hoarded (wealth)) in the life of the world (and withheld it) he put it in a container and refused to give the right of Allah which is due from it."
  70,20,"(Fretful) he is not patient (when evil befalleth him) when poverty and hardship befall him"
  70,22,"(Save worshippers) those who pray the five daily prayers for they are not like this."
  70,25,"(For the beggar) who ask you to give him from your wealth (and the destitute) who is denied his wage or booty; it is also said that this refers to the artisan whose skill does not earn him enough for him to subsist; it is also said that this refers to the poor who does not beg from others and as a result no one gives or knows about him;"
  70,27,"(And those who are fearful of their Lord's doom"
  70,28,"Lo! the doom of their Lord is that before which none can feel secure) no guarantee of security has come to them from their Lord."
  70,29,"(And those who preserve their chastity) they are chaste as far as what is unlawful is concerned"
  70,38,"Doth every man among them hope to enter the Garden of Delight?) This is an answer from Allah to the disbelievers that He will not let them enter the Garden."